      "value_type": "Bool",
      "takes_value": false,
      "description": "using this option without --expand, ntfsresize will determine the theoretically smallest shrunken filesystem size supported.  Most of the time the result is the space already used on the filesystem. Ntfsresize will refuse shrinking to a smaller size than  what  you got by this option and depending on several factors it might be unable to shrink very close to this theoretical size. Although the in‐ tegrity  of  your data should be never in risk, it's still strongly recommended to make a test run by using the --no-action option be‐ fore real resizing.",
