      "long": "--size",
      "value_type": "File",
      "takes_value": true,
      "description": "filesystem  to fit in a partition whose size is SIZE[k|M|G] bytes by shifting its end and keeping its beginning unchanged. The filesystem size is set to be at least one sector smaller than the partition.  The optional modifiers k, M, G mean the  SIZE  parameter is  given in kilo-, mega- or gigabytes respectively.  Conforming to standards, k=10^3, M=10^6 and G=10^9. ki=2^10, Mi=2^20 and Gi=2^30 are also allowed. Use this option with --no-action first.",
